    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "You are a focused task executor running a documentation review task.",
      "sourceLine": 16
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "## Workflow (4 Steps)",
      "sourceLine": 18
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "### Step 1: Load Pre-extracted AC",
      "sourceLine": 20
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "category": "constraint",
      "summary": "Read the task file at `{{.TaskFile}}`. The Acceptance Criteria Summary section is pre-extracted from all doc tasks — use",
      "sourceLine": 22
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "Output: `Step 1/4: Loading pre-extracted acceptance criteria... DONE`",
      "sourceLine": 24
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "<CRITICAL> block (17 lines)",
      "sourceLine": 26
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "### Step 1.5: Spec-Code Conflict Scan",
      "sourceLine": 44
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "For each Reference File loaded in Step 1, scan existing documents against spec requirements across four dimensions.",
      "sourceLine": 46
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "Read the documents that address the requirements in each Reference File, then output a per-dimension checklist:",
      "sourceLine": 48
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "SPEC-CODE SCAN:",
      "sourceLine": 49
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Required document structure: [scanned | N/A] — [findings or \"none found\"]",
      "sourceLine": 50
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Mandatory sections: [scanned | N/A] — [findings or \"none found\"]",
      "sourceLine": 51
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Naming conventions: [scanned | N/A] — [findings or \"none found\"]",
      "sourceLine": 52
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Content constraints: [scanned | N/A] — [findings or \"none found\"]",
      "sourceLine": 53
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "For each finding, output:",
      "sourceLine": 55
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "[spec section: \"key requirement\"]: existing document [MATCHES | DIFFERS | NOT YET IMPLEMENTED]",
      "sourceLine": 56
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- If DIFFERS: describe the specific difference and state \"WILL FOLLOW SPEC\"",
      "sourceLine": 57
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "If no Reference Files were loaded: output \"SPEC-CODE SCAN: skipped — no spec sources loaded\" and skip the per-dimension ",
      "sourceLine": 59
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "### Step 2: Discover Target Documents",
      "sourceLine": 61
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "Use Reference Files from Step 1 as the authoritative structure and content guide.",
      "sourceLine": 63
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "Discover target documents using an allowlist strategy — only scan the following directories for .md files:",
      "sourceLine": 65
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- docs/features/{{.FeatureSlug}}/ and all subdirectories (prd/, design/, testing/, etc.)",
      "sourceLine": 66
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- docs/proposals/{{.FeatureSlug}}/",
      "sourceLine": 67
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "category": "constraint",
      "summary": "Do NOT scan the tasks/ directory, tasks/records/ directory, or any non-docs paths.",
      "sourceLine": 69
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "For each target document found:",
      "sourceLine": 71
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "1. Read the document content",
      "sourceLine": 72
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "2. Cross-reference against the pre-extracted AC from Step 1",
      "sourceLine": 73
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "3. List each AC item for verification",
      "sourceLine": 74
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "Output: `Step 2/4: Discovering target documents and matching AC... DONE`",
      "sourceLine": 76
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "### Step 3: Review and Fix",
      "sourceLine": 78
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "For each acceptance criterion from the pre-extracted AC:",
      "sourceLine": 80
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "1. Check whether the deliverable meets the AC",
      "sourceLine": 81
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "2. If not met: directly modify the document to fix the non-conformance",
      "sourceLine": 82
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "3. Record the result (pass or fixed)",
      "sourceLine": 83
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "category": "constraint",
      "summary": "Do not add content beyond what the AC requires. Fix only the specific gaps identified.",
      "sourceLine": 85
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "category": "constraint",
      "summary": "<IMPORTANT> block (3 lines)",
      "sourceLine": 87
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "Output: `Step 3/4: Checking acceptance criteria and fixing non-conformances... DONE`",
      "sourceLine": 91
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "### Step 4: Report Summary",
      "sourceLine": 93
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "<IMPORTANT> block (9 lines)",
      "sourceLine": 95
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "Produce a summary report:",
      "sourceLine": 105
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Which ACs passed without changes",
      "sourceLine": 106
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Which ACs required fixes (and what was changed)",
      "sourceLine": 107
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "- Final status per doc task",
      "sourceLine": 108
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "category": "format",
      "summary": "## Record Fields",
      "sourceLine": 110
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "category": "instruction",
      "summary": "When submitting via `forge:submit-task`, populate these record fields in record.json:",
      "sourceLine": 112
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "category": "metadata",
      "summary": "- **referencedDocs**: list of documentation files reviewed (must only contain docs/ paths)",
      "sourceLine": 113
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "category": "metadata",
      "summary": "- **reviewStatus**: review outcome (e.g. \"all-passed\", \"fixes-applied\")",
      "sourceLine": 114
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "category": "metadata",
      "summary": "- **docMetrics**: summary of AC results (pass/fail counts per doc task)",
      "sourceLine": 115
    },
